      <h2>Day 2:- Kharna.</h2>
      <p>
        The second day is called Kharna and falls on 29th October. Vratis
        observe fast for the entire day of kharna. In the evening, the prasad of
        jaggery pudding is prepared on the earthen stove. When the puja is
        concluded, the vratti break their fast by eating the jaggery kheer and
        ghee layered Roti as Prasad and later on it is distributed among family
        and friends. On the mid night of Kharna people prepare thekua- a special
        Prasad for Chhathi Maiya. After having this prasad distribution, Vratis
        begin an arduous nirjala fast (without water) lasting for next 36 hours.
      </p>
