      <h2>Day 3:- Sandhya Arghya.</h2>
      <p>
        After that, On 30th October will be the third day. During the day, the
        daura (a basket made of bamboo sticks) is prepared by putting into it
        all the offerings including thekua and seasonal fruits. In the evening
        of the third day, rituals take place at the banks of the river which
        include fasting, holy bathing and meditation where all the devotees
        offer ‘arghya’ to the setting sun called Sandhya Arghya. Folk songs
        (Chhath Geet) are also sung that show the social culture.
      </p>
